Mythic wants to nullify mez in RvR, right?  We want mind to be useful in RvR while Mythic does its evil deeds, right?  I propose 2 additions to the mind line that should make it attractive while not overpowering us in PvE.<P>1) The popular suggestion form many sorcerers is an aoe unmez.  I think that's a great idea to offset (a little) our lack of insta-casts.<P>2) Being the masters of mind magic(hehe) Why not have a buff in the mind spec that makes us immune to mez.  Something like<BR>level 30ish - Immune to Mez<BR>level 40ish - Immune to Mez and Stun<BR>Level 50 - Immune to Mez, stun, and root<P>This would be self only so not overpowering, and it could have a duration so you could still get caught without it.  If a mez immunity self buff is too much, maybe make our unmez ability work on ourselves at some point.
