Putting an AEunmezz in the Mind line makes a lot of sense to me. It would keep us as back row casters, waiting until our forces are mezzed, then unmezzing them and starting their 1 min timer. Then we can proceed to AeMezz.. even with diminishing returns and the resist rates, I'm sure we would get a couple mezzed here or there and it would in my mind be a decent defense to the insta mez. Not to mention, we already have problems acting as Albion's primary mezzer when we are competing against chain wearing casters with insta... this would make our role the same, but the tactics completely different. Personally, the AEUnmezz would make me spec high mind. I rolled a sorc to be a support class, not to be a nuker. As it stands now, the only way i can actually help my realm is to be a nuker.   <IMG SRC="frown.gif" border="0"> <P>As for the charm in base line... I can see the pros and cons. <P>Pro: Quix's pet guide would be even more popular, and he'd get even more noob questions [muhahahahaahahahahahaha] <P>Con: Quix's pet guide would be even more popular, and he'd get even more noob questions [muhahahahaahahahahahaha] <P>  <IMG SRC="biggrin.gif" border="0"><P>--------------------<P>Chiara Fulkerson -  40 Sorceress<BR>Keepers of the Blade - High Council<BR>Beloved wife of Phansian Fulkerson - 40 Armsman<BR>Meekrobe is my hero...<BR><A HREF="http://www.angelfire.com/rant/farout2" TARGET=_blank>**~`My reality check just bounced`~**</A>
