I like the idea of a baseline charm, but Mythic has a habit of giving and taking in the same patch.  What if they moved it to baseline and to offset that power, they revert it back to only charming humanoid?<P>I think a better solution is to keep charm like it is, and let us charm ANYTHING in the game save guards.  Add reptiles, undead, etc., and you make charming much better and more attractive for RvR.  I think the biggest drawback about pets in RvR is not that they aren't useful, but rather finding new ones after you get killed.<P>Change the matter nuke as some people have already said.  Change the body nuke to some other resist.  Give us some form of AE or group Cure Mez, and more available pets.  That would go a long way towards making sorcerers more attractive to play, just by expanding what we can already do.<P>--------------------<P><B>Gyles</B>-Level 49 Sorcerer<BR><B>Lydon Sharpe</B>-Level 41 Mercenary<BR><B>Brief Encounter</B>-Level 23 Scout<BR>Defenders of the Mithril Tower<BR>Galahad Server
