Confuse is one of the msot useful spells to a Sorceror soloing with a pet. And Amnesia is possibly the most underrated, and underutilized spell in the game. Groups love you when you cast that and ALL aggro turns off casters and healers, and goes to the paladin chanting his heal. And it's range and interruptions in RvR make it far from useless.<P>Look, every time we do this, some people say certain spells are worthless, and others live and die by them. We have a lot of spells that can be used very well by different people. One mans trash is another mans treasure.<P>But moving the charm to baseline woudl kill any reason to spec mind. Then we decide where to dump the points between body and matter. NEITHER of these are the unique line of the Sorceror. We would be closer to the Cabalist then.<P>I know CC is hammered at every turn. I know many people want the easier choices of speccing by making one, or even 2 lines, near worthless. Takes away all the hard decisions doesn't it?<P>But we do not need to give up on the Mind line or CC. We need to fight to make the line viable, and to restore us to a position of being able to perform the prime CC duty. Noone else in Albion can do it as well as the other realms prime CC'er. We overcome this with numbers. The game favors faster damage, so longer, more controlled fights are a thing of the past.<P>Screw that. I don't play counter strike. We need viable and effective CC that our realm so desparately needs in PvE (in a limited fashion as of late) and in RvR (where we are getting our asses handed to us).<P>The easy way out is not the best way. Fight till we actually get what we need, and what the realm as a whole needs.<P>I ordered a Bic Mac damnnit! Two Cheeseburgers and a cherry pie ain't gonna cut it. I don't care if it is as much food, it is not the food we ordered.<P>--------------------<P>i3ullseye<BR>"You're good, but me? I'm Magic!"<P>Rictus -Sorceror(DAOC)/Rictus(EQ)<BR>DAOC Sorceror team lead...<P>Please visit our <A HREF