Well, CC is obviously nerfed to oblivion, so what else can we do?<P>We have Support Spells, and we have Damage Spells.<P>Our Support ones (debuffs) do NOTHING.  So *all* we're left is Damage.  Is it any wonder that Mind is going to be the most unlikely to be a primary spec?<P>How well does a Primary Mind Sorcerer survive in RvR, eh?  The *only* thing they get for going past 34 in Mind is another useless debuff, and a slightly, every so slightly stronger Nerfed Mez.  That's it.<P>As for Mind Baseline, yes, I consent Bullseye that those spells are useful....in PvE.  However, Amnesia loses half it's usefullness in RvR, and Confuse loses *all* of it!  Why should only half your spells in a line be deemed useless once you reach level 50?  And I think there's no arguements that Mind needs something to make it *worth* primarily speccing in, something that maybe works this time (instead of half-assed debuffs and a mez that has been neutered).  Right now, people feel obligated to take mind to 32 at least just to get that walking DoT that we call a pet.  Then they pop it up two more for the next AE Mez, and then, if they're like me, they never think about Mind again.  Two spells in a spec line?  Is that all there should be?  Two spells, one's been neutered to oblivion, and the other is debatably useful.
