<HR size="1" color="#12350C">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
What was the last class that did have a sweeping change made to their primary weapon, but then soon afterwards had a sweeping positive change to compensate?<P>I don't think I can remember anyone who has started out with one powerful weapon, had it nerfed to hell, and then later be given a different weapon of equal usefullness but more moderate power as far as usefullness. (IE, nerfing an overpowered ability to hell, but then giving that class something just as useful and effective, but not so overpowered).<P>It has historically always been Huge Nerfs, but never Huge Compensations.  The closest they've gotten is Camo vs. See Hidden as being a "huge compensation".  It makes Stealth just the way it used to be, except it's on a timer.  They can't find the middle ground anywhere, they can't have Assassins find Archers sometimes, and miss them the other times.<P>It's just always been powerful nerfs with sissy compensation (the Strike-Out Team giving us a Snare-DD in Matter was interesting, not unique.  And the addition of a second AE Dex/Qui Debuff in the same line made me lose all faith).
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#12350C">
